ScanSoft was formerly know as Visioneer Inc, a hardware and software scanner company. The latter bought ScanSoft, a Xerox Corporation spin-off, back in 1999, and incorporated ScanSoft as a company name. Nuance posted USD 1.92bn in revenues in 2014. McDonald's is present in 119 countries with more than 36,000 restaurants and about 440,000 employees around the world. ORIGINAL Colombian energy group Empresa de Energia de Bogota SA ESP (EEB) announced an agreement to acquire a 51% stake in four electricity transmission concessions in Brazil from Brazilian peer Desenvix Energias Renovaveis SA and Panamanian conglomerate Grupo J. Malucelli, for USD 170mn. The sellers acted through their Brazilian subsidiaries J. Malucelli Energia SA and J. Malucelli Construtora de Obras SA, respectively. The companies - Transenergia Renovavel SA, Transenergia Sao Paulo SA and Transenergia Goias SA - are Special Purpose Entities (SPEs) and are part of energy group Grupo Transenergia. The latter is controlled by Eletrobras Furnas (49%) and J. Malucelli (51%). The fourth concession is MGE Transmissao whose ownership is divided between J. Malucelli Energia SA (25.5%) and Desenvix (25.5%). The contracts have a term of 25 years. The concessions have a length of 1,094 km and cover voltages of 500, 345, 230 and 138 kV, and are located in the following states: Espirito Santo, Goias, Mato Grosso, Mato Grosso do Sul, Minas Gerais and Sao Paulo. Ricardo Roa Barragán, President of EEB said that the acquisition is part of a USD 1.8bn investment approved by the company's board to be applied in Latin America until 2019. He also stated that Brazil is the country of the region with the highest expected growth in energy infrastructure. EIG Global Energy Partners LLC, headquartered in Washington, DC, USA, is a private equity firm specialised in investments in energy projects, companies, and related infrastructure with more than USD 15.4bn in assets under management on behalf of pension plans, insurance companies, endowments, foundations and sovereign wealth funds in the United States, Asia and Europe. Since its inception in 1982, EIG has invested more than USD 21.4bn in 300 portfolio investments in 35 countries in the North and South America, Europe, Asia and Oceania. With a team of 90 professionals, the company operates seven offices in Washington, DC, Houston, London, Sydney, Hong Kong, Seoul, and Rio de Janeiro. Abengoa SA, founded in 1941, provides technology solutions for sustainable development in the energy and environment sectors. The company operates in three segments: engineering and construction, concession-type infrastructure and industrial production. It is engaged in the generation of electricity from renewable sources, in the manufacturing of biofuels, in the construction of infrastructures in the energy sector, as well as in the desalination of seawater and recycling of industrial waste. Abengoa reported sales revenues of EUR 7.15bn (USD 8.69bn) and net income of EUR 21.9mn (USD 26.6mn) in 2014. The deal is pending regulatory approvals. Midia Resources SRL owns interests in four oil and gas license blocks in the Romanian Black Sea - 65% operated interest in each of blocks 13 Pelican and 15 Midia, a 50% operated interest in block 25 Luceafarul and a 40% non-operated interest in block 27 Muridava. The four assets are estimated to have net 2C (Best estimate of contingent resources) of 51 mmboe and net Prospective resources of 375 mmboe. The company will focus on its assets in the North Sea instead. The Pelican natural gas field is being explored by Austrian energy company OMV and U.S. oil and gas group Exxon Mobil Corp. The Lucafarul and Muridava natural gas fields were discovered in 2013. The total proven reserves (1P) of Luceafarul block are around 104 bcf (3 km3). The total estimated resources of the Muridava block are around 169 bcf (4.85 km3). Both blocks are expected to begin production in 2018. CIEP, established in May 2013, focuses on mid- and downstream oil and gas exploration and production, refining and marketing, and oil field services in Europe, Africa, Latin America and Asia. The Carlyle Group is a global alternative investment firm with USD 194bn in assets under management. It specialises in private equity investments in the aerospace, defence, consumer and retail, energy, financial services, healthcare, industrial, technology and business services, telecommunications, media and transportation sectors. Sterling is engaged in the exploration, appraisal and development of crude oil and natural gas in the UK, Romania, the Netherlands and France. It is listed on the Toronto Stock Exchange Venture. ORIGINAL: Oman-based investment company Dhofar International Development & Investment (DIGIC), Japanese conglomerate Mitsui, and Saudi Arabian power company ACWA Power have signed an agreement to acquire Oman-based Dhofar Generating Company (DGC). The consortium of three companies have won bid to build and operate Salalah-2, power generation project. 400 MW natural gas-fired combined cycle power plant will be located in the Salalah Industrial Area, southern Oman. ORIGINAL: U.S. processed foods manufacturers H.J. Heinz Co and Kraft Foods Group Inc announced they have agreed to merge their operations to create The Kraft Heinz Co, forming the fifth largest food and beverage company in the world. Under the agreement, Kraft shareholders will receive 49% of the stock in the combined entity, plus a special cash dividend of USD 16.50 a share, while current Heinz shareholders will own 51% on a fully diluted basis. U.S. tycoon Warren Buffett's investment company Berkshire Hathaway Inc and Brazilian investment firm 3G Capital Gestora de Recursos Ltda will participate with an equity contribution of nearly USD 10bn, part of which will go to pay for the aggregate special dividend to be distributed to the shareholders of Kraft Foods. The transaction is subject to approval by Kraft's shareholders, as well as to regulatory and other approvals. The deal is estimated to take place in the second half of 2015. According to the official press release, the parties estimate the target company's annual revenues at approximately USD 28bn. Alex Behring, Heinz's Chairman and Managing Partner of 3G Capital, will be appointed Chairman of new company and John Cahill, Kraft's Chairman and CEO, will be appointed Vice-chairman. Heinz's CEO Bernardo Hees will become CEO of The Kraft Heinz Co. The Kraft Heinz Co will be headquartered in Pittsburgh and in Chicago, U.S.A. In June 2013, Berkshire Hathaway Inc and 3G Capital acquired the total capital of H.J. Heinz Company for USD 23.2bn. H.J. Heinz Co, founded in 1869, is an international processed food manufacturer and distributor with operations in 200 countries on six continents. Its product portfolio comprises ketchup, sauces, meals, soups, potato products, snacks and infant nutrition. The company is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) and posted USD 10.92bn in revenues and a net income of USD 672.39mn FY Ended 28 December 2014. Kraft Foods Group Inc, founded in 2013 as a spin off from Kraft Foods Inc, is one of North America's largest consumer packaged food and beverage companies. The company's iconic brands include Kraft, Capri Sun, Jell-O, Kool-Aid, Lunchables, Maxwell House, Oscar Mayer, Philadelphia, Planters and Velveeta. Kraft employs more than 22,000 people in the U.S. and Canada. The company is listed on the NASDAQ Stock Exchange and posted USD 18.22bn in revenues and a net profit of USD 2.72bn FY 28 December 2013. Berkshire Hathaway Inc, established in 1889 in Omaha, Nebraska, USA, is an investment management firm, focused on investments in a variety of industries, including property and casualty insurance and reinsurance, utilities and energy, freight rail transportation, finance, manufacturing, retailing and services. Chairman and CEO of Berkshire is Warren Buffet, one of the world's wealthiest people. The company is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) and posted USD 140.31bn in revenues and a net profit of USD 19.85bn in 2013. 3G Capital, launched in 2004 by Brazilian private investors Jorge Lemann, Marcel Telles, and Carlos Sicupira, and based in New York and Rio de Janeiro, is a global investment firm focused on long-term value, with a particular emphasis on maximizing the potential of brands and businesses. The firm completed the acquisition of U.S. fast food restaurants Burger King for USD 3.3bn in October 2010 and has investments in Belgian-Brazilian brewing company Anheuser-Busch InBev, U.K.-based automotive parts producer Delphi Automotive PLC, U.S. consumer goods marketer Newell Rubbermaid Inc, U.S. oil and gas exploration and production company Anadarko Petroleum Corp, and Brazilian online retail company B2W Companhia Global do Varejo. _______________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 2 de Julho de 2015, a Kraft anunciou a conclusão do negócio. ORIGINAL: U.K.-based resources and development company Vast Resources Plc announced it will acquire a 80% stake in Romanian polymetallic mining company Mineral Mining SA, the owner of Băița Bihor mine, for a total consideration of EUR 1.22mn (USD 1.32mn). The acquisition is in line with Vast Resources' development strategy to build an established portfolio with a strong presence in Romania. As part of the deal agreement, the buyer will assume the obligation to pay all the creditors of Mineral Mining. Băița Bihor is located in the Apuseni Mountains, Transylvania, an area which hosts Romania's largest polymetallic and uranium mines, 50 km away from Romania's largest Au-Cu mine, Rosia Montana (> 10 Moz Au) and also from Rosia Poiena, which contains over one billion tons of porphyry copper ore. Băița Bihor mine is estimated to contain 1,800,000 tons of polymetallic ore (gold, silver, copper, zinc, lead, tungsten and molybdenum). Mineral Mining SA, founded in 2008, is engaged in the extraction and processing of polymetallic minerals with a total mining capacity of 10,000 tpm (tons per month). The company has not conducted any operations since August 2013 and it has filled for insolvency proceedings as of December 2014. Vast Resources, former African Consolidated Resources, is focused on recommencing production at previously producing mines and has a portfolio of exploration and development projects in Romania and Southern Africa. A empresa concentra-se no setor agrícola e tem 15 anos de experiência no mercado brasileiro e em mais 13 países da América Latina. Pioneira no mercado brasileiro, a PRG tem sido reconhecida como líder em questões de gestão de clientes e vendas e estratégias de marketing. A PRG Brasil tem um foco de longa data e de conhecimentos sobre as vendas de insumos agrícolas e gestão de distribuição. A AGDATA LP, fundada em 1985 e sediada em Charlotte, Carolina do Norte, EUA, fornece soluções estratégicas de dados, incluindo a gestão terceirizada de banco de dados, administração de programas de marketing, coleta de dados, serviços de dados e análise. A AGDATA é líder no fornecimento de dados estratégicos e soluções analíticas para os maiores provedores de saúde e empresas de culturas agrícolas e animais do mundo. A empresa tem negócios direto com mais de 9,500 revendedores e distribuidores da indústria, que representam mais de 90% do mercado dos EUA. ORIGINAL: Franco-Belgian entrepreneur and investor Pierre Louvrier said his vehicle LIC33 will acquire certain stakes in several Bulgarian companies from former local banker Tsvetan Vasilev for a token price of EUR 1.0 and assuming their total net debt of around EUR 900mn. The transaction is subject to regulatory approvals. The assets include a 43% stake in telecoms group Bulgarian Telecommunications Company (BTC), a 91% stake in military munitions and explosives manufacturer Dunarit, a 91% stake in military aircraft repair company Avionams, TV audience research firm GARB, digital terrestrial television First Digital, and other minor assets. The deal includes also TV and radio broadcasting services NURTS, which is in the process of being wholly-acquired by BTC. BTC is the former fixed line incumbent and the country's third largest mobile service provider, operating under the Vivacom brand. It has 1.2 million subscribers and employs over 3,500. Its annual EBITDA is EUR 165-170mn, while its debt is approximately EUR 400mn, according to the buyer. The group is 33%-owned by Russia's second largest lender VTB. LIC33 said it will also propose to acquire the shares held by other shareholders of BTC by the end of 2015. NURTS owns and operates 700 infrastructure towers across Bulgaria, providing signal transmission and radio, and TV broadcasting services. It has an annual EBITDA of EUR 8-9mn and debt of EUR 12mn. Dunarit manufactures artillery and aerial ammunition, antitank and antipersonnel mines, detonating cords and other machinery for civil use. The company is based in the Danube port city Ruse and employs over 700. The company has an annual EBITDA of EUR 16mn and debt of EUR 25mn. Avionams is military jet and helicopter repair and maintenance provider. Its facilities are located at Graf Ignatievo military airbase near Plovdiv, southern Bulgaria. Its annual EBITDA stands at EUR 5-10mn and its debt is approximately EUR 8mn. Garb is the leading provider of TV audience research services and data in Bulgaria. The company analyses audience response to broadcasting and advertisement of 35 TV channels and 18 radio stations in the country. First Digital is the digital terrestrial television (DTT) multiplex operator for Bulgarian National Television and other TV channels. The total EBITDA of these companies is estimated at EUR 180-200mn, according to the buyer LIC33. Louvrier said LIC33 will be looking to restructure the companies' debts, most of which are considered to be owed to bankrupt Corporate Commercial Bank. The latter is majority-owned by Tsvetan Vasilev. The license of Corporate Commercial Bank, Bulgaria's fourth largest lender, was revoked by the country's central bank in early November 2014 after the bank faced liquidity problems earlier in the year. The deal was announced in a press release from the General Superintendence of Brazilian antitrust competition regulator CADE. CADE is concerned with the high level of concentration in the pharmaceutical hard capsules manufacturing sector, since here is only one competitor in the Brazilian market that produces hard capsules. The acquisition, said CADE, would grant Capsugel a near monopoly, owning more than 90% of the Brazilian market of hard capsules. The operation was notified in November 2014, and will have to go through CADE's Tribunal which will be responsible for the final decision on the approval. The legal deadline to the final decision is 240 days, extendable for 90 more days. Genix Industria Farmaceutica Ltda, founded in 2011 and based in Anapolis, Goias, the main hub of the pharmaceutical Brazil, is a leading manufacturer of empty hard gelatin capsules. The company's main product is Extracaps, a registered trademark of empty hard capsules. Capsugel Inc, founded in 1963 and based in Morristown, New Jersey, USA, is a global leader in delivering high-quality, innovative dosage forms and solutions to its customers in the health care industry. The company's Hard Capsule business offers customers a portfolio of gelatin, vegetarian, and other specialised capsule technologies. Capsugel's Dosage Form Solutions (DFS) business utilises an array of proprietary technologies and specialised manufacturing capabilities, including bioavailability enhancement, modified release, abuse deterrence, biotherapeutic processing, and inhalation formulation. The acquisition by ChemChina will help Pirelli enhance its presence in the Chinese market and improve its competitiveness against rivals Michelin and Continental. The company manufactures tires for buses, heavy trucks, SUVs, light commercial vehicles and motorcycles. The company had net debt of EUR 980mn (USD 1.24bn) as of end-September 2014. China National Chemical Corp produces various chemical materials, basic chemical products, petrochemical products and chemical equipment. Camfin SpA invests in automotive companies in addition to producing tires and providing real estate asset management services. Sinagro produces crude vegetable oils, except corn oil, also leases machinery and construction equipment. UPL, formerly known as United Phosphorus, established in 1969 and headquartered in Mumbai, India, is an international manufacturer and marketer of generic crop protection products, chemicals and seeds. The company operates manufacturing plants in India, Argentina, China, Colombia, Spain, France, the Netherlands, Italy, the United Kingdom and Vietnam, and has some 3,600 employees. It has offices in Barueri, Rio de Janeiro and Ribeirao Preto and employs about 500 people. PwC Brasil, founded in 1915 and based in Sao Paulo, is the Brazilian branch of PriceWaterhouseCooper, and provides a network of separate and independent firms working in an integrated way in providing business consultancy, tax consulting and corporate, audit and outsourcing services. PwC Brasil has about 5,300 professionals across 19 offices in all regions of Brazil. PwC, founded in 1849 and located in New York, USA, is a global auditing, accounting, and assurance services firm. It provides IFRS reporting, valuation, human resources, accounting advisory, and forensic services. The firm was formerly known as Price, Waterhouse & Co. and changed its name to PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP in 1998. Through its branches, PwC has businesses in 157 countries, employing more than 184,000 people. PwC is one of the Big Four auditors, along with Deloitte, EY and KPMG and the 5th-largest privately owned organization in the United States as of 2014. PwC posted USD 34bn in revenues in 2014, of which USD 15.1bn was generated by its Assurance practice, USD 8.8bn by its Tax practice and USD 10bn by its Advisory practice. TMF Group, established in 1988 and headquartered in Amsterdam, Netherlands, is a global management and outsourcing accounting group. It provides financial, legal and human resource administrative services. The group has 84 offices throughout 75 countries across the Americas, Asia Pacific, Europe and the Middle East. It has a strong presence in Latin America and the Caribbean, with offices in Costa Rica, the British Virgin Islands, Dominican Republic, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Jamaica, Netherland Antilles, Nicaragua, Panama, Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Chile, Colombia, Ecuador, Mexico, Paraguay, Peru, Uruguay and Venezuela. The group employs 3,000 people. ORIGINAL: U.S. television and the Internet content developer Scripps Networks Interactive said it will acquire a 52.7% stake in Polish multi-platform media company TVN from Polish media and entertainment group ITI Group and France's Canal+ Group for EUR 584mn (USD 612.8mn). Scripps Networks will also assume EUR 840mn (USD 881.3mn) of debt. The transaction is subject to regulatory approvals. Upon completion, Scripps Networks will have to launch a mandatory public tender offer to minority shareholders. The acquisition is in line with Scripps Networks' ongoing strategic development of international business, and provides it with a further scale in Europe. In 2011, the U.S. company entered a partnership with BBC Worldwide in the UK for the UKTV portfolio of 10 entertainment and lifestyle channels. TVN is one of the leading media companies in Poland. Its portfolio of free-to-air and pay TV lifestyle and entertainment channels include TVN, TVN 7, TVN Style, TTV, and TVN Turbo, as well as Poland's leading 24 hour news channel TVN24, and business news channel TVN24 Biznes i Swiat. The group has the largest market share of 22% of Polish viewing in 2014. TVN Media is the country's leading advertising sales house for 2014 with a 33% market share in advertising revenue for TVN's own portfolio of channels, as well as selling advertising for a number of other commercial broadcasters in Poland. TVN had consolidated revenues of PLN 1.59bn (EUR 380.9mn) in 2014. Scripps Networks distributes seven lifestyle brands including HGTV, Food Network, Travel Channel, DIY Network, Cooking Channel, Fine Living and Asian Food Channel, reaching more than 220 million subscribers in nearly 180 countries in Europe, Middle East, Africa, Asia Pacific, Latin America and the Caribbean. It had total revenues of USD 2.67bn in 2014. ITI Group is the leading Polish media and entertainment group, active in television and online broadcasting. Canal+ Group is the leading pay-TV company in France with operations also in Africa, Poland and Vietnam. The group has a total subscription base of 15.3 million. It is also present in the free-to-air television broadcasting, with three national channels and advertising sales division. Through its subsidiary STUDIOCANAL, CANAL+ Group is a European leader in motion picture and TV series production and distribution. The group has annual revenues of EUR 5.3bn and over 6,000 employees. 2015.11.10 2044.15 1162.76 　 　 　 　 　 负值 43.60 70.50 来源 1 来源 2 5.06 财政年度 2014

ORIGINAL: Singapore-listed IT and professional services provider Armarda Group Ltd said it will acquire 90% of Hong Kong-based SinoCloud HK from private investors for HKD 137.9mn (USD 17.8mn). The acquisition is subject to fulfilment of certain conditions. The purchase consideration will be partially satisfied in cash or assignment of receivables and partially through the issuance of new Armarda shares. Upon completion of the deal, SinoCloud HK will control 70% interest in China-based internet data center services and businesses operator Guiyang Zhongdian. Guiyang Zhongdian provides internet data centre, cloud computing and big data services with a data storage facility in the Guiyang region, which went operational in October 2014. The facility comprises 660 cabinets and hosts up to 6,600 data servers. The company has signed a strategic cooperation framework agreement with China Telecom Company Limited. The remaining 30% of the interest in Guiyang Zhongdian is held by Shanghai Ronghuan Industrial Co. Ltd. Guiyang Zhongdian had net asset value of CNY 14.4mn (USD 2.3mn) at the end of 2014. The acquisition will allow Armarda to expand its business in China and further develop its existing operations in the areas of information technology and communications through leveraging on Guiyang Zhongdian's data centre business and its local network. Armarda Group is an IT and professional services provider serving banking and financial services industry in China. Currently its operations are established mainly in Hong Kong, Beijing, Shanghai and Zhuhai. ORIGINAL: German private equity investment firm Triton Beratungsgesellschaft GmbH announced it has agreed to sell its subsidiary COMPO Expert GmbH, a Germany-based fertilizers manufacturer, to Hong Kong-based alternative investment firm Xio Group. Financial terms were not disclosed. Triton said that it will retain ownership of the COMPO Consumer business, involved in the supply of branded goods for home and garden. The German PE firm added that the sale of the COMPO Expert segment will allow it to focus on the COMPO Consumer business where it sees growth opportunities in all European markets. COMPO Expert is engaged in the manufacturing and sale of high-quality, innovative special fertilizers and plant protection products such as slow-release fertilizers, special mineral fertilizers, coated fertilizers, nutrient salts, liquid fertilizers, trace nutrients and others. The company generates annual revenues of approximately EUR 450mn (USD 476mn). COMPO Expert operates in more than 17 countries across Europe, North and South America, and Asia. In Latin America the company is present in Argentina, Brazil, Chile and Mexico. XIO Group is a global, multi-billion dollar alternative investments firm with offices in London, Hong Kong, and Shanghai. It has more than USD 3bn of committed capital for global transactions. Triton is a private equity company focused on investing in medium-sized companies in Northern Europe, Italy and Spain, which operate in the business services, health, industrial, and consumer sectors. 2015.06.05 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 负值 　 　 来源 1 来源 2

The new company will be named Healthways Brasil. Healthways acted through its subsidiary Healthways International. Local news portal Exame.com reported that Sul America will invest BRL 250mn in the joint venture through the transfer of 30,000 of its own health management contracts to the new company. The amount invested by Healthways International was not disclosed. The partnership aims to explore health and well-being improvement programs in Brazil, directly to employers, public entities and governments, private health plans, providers and individuals throughout the country. Furthermore, the operation is impulsed by the fact that the Brazilian private health insurance system is the second largest in the world, covering more than 50 million lives or almost 25 percent of the population, according to the official press release. Healthways Brasil will be the exclusive well-being provider to Sul América's 2 million health plan members. According to official news, Sul America will elect two-out-of-five Board members of Healthways Brasil and will have a 49% ownership, with the remnant seats filled by Healthways with the remaining 51% ownership. Ben R. Leedle, Jr., President and CEO of Healthways said that “this joint venture is another step forward in our global strategy of partnering with organizations that are at risk for health-related costs, whether direct medical costs, indirect costs associated with lost productivity, or both". Sul America SA, founded in 1895, is the third largest healthcare operator and fourth largest auto insurer in Brazil, in terms of premiums. The company provides health, dental, auto, elementary risks, life insurance, private pension, health care management, asset management services, and premium savings bonds to more than seven million clients. Sul America has a distribution network of 30,000 independent insurance brokers and partners with more than 20 financial and retail institutions with 16,000 points of sale. Listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange, Sul America SA posted BRL 13.5bn (USD 5.02bn) in net insurance premiums and a net profit of BRL 548.7mn (USD 204.2mn) in 2014. Its total assets amounted to BRL 21.6bn (USD 8.04bn) as of 31 December 2014. Healthways Inc, established in 1981 and based in Cool Springs, Tennessee, USA, is the largest independent global provider of well-being improvement solutions. Its customers include include employers, integrated health systems, hospitals, physicians, health plans, communities, and government entities. The company serves approximately 68 million people across four continents. Listed on the NASDAQ Stock Exchange, Healthways Inc posted USD 742.2mn in revenues and a net loss of USD 5.6mn in 2014. _______________________________________________________________________________ A Healthways Inc, empresa americana de bem-estar e saúde anunciou um acordo com a seguradora brasileira independente Sul América SA de modo a formar uma joint venture no sector de bem-estar e saúde. A nova empresa chamar-se-á Healthways Brasil. A Healthways atuou através de sua subsidiária Healthways International. O Portal de notícias local Exame.com informou que a Sul América vai investir BRL 250mn na joint venture através da transferência de 30,000 de seus próprios contratos de gestão de saúde para a nova empresa. O valor investido pela Healthways Internacional não foi divulgado. A parceria tem como objetivo explorar programas de saúde e bem-estar no Brasil, diretamente para os empregadores, entidades públicas e governos, planos de saúde privados, prestadores e indivíduos em todo o país. Além disso, a operação é impulsionada pelo fato de que o sistema de seguro de saúde privado brasileiro ser o segundo maior do mundo, cobrindo mais de 50 milhões de vidas ou quase 25 por cento da população, de acordo com o comunicado de imprensa oficial. A Healthways Brasil tornar-se-á assim o provedor de bem-estar exclusivo para 2 milhões de beneficiários de planos de saúde da Sul América. A Sul America vai igualmente poder eleger dois-em-cinco dos membros do Conselho de Administração da Healthways Brasil e terá uma participação de 49%, com os lugares remanescentes a serem preenchidos pela Healthways com a restante participação de 51%. Ben R. Leedle, Jr., Presidente e diretor executivo da Healthways disse que "esta joint venture é mais um passo em frente na nossa estratégia global de parcerias com organizações que estão em risco devido a custos relacionados com a saúde, sejam eles custos médicos diretos os custos indirectos associados com perda de produtividade, ou ambos". A Sul América, fundada em 1895, é a terceira maior operadora de saúde e a quarta maior seguradora de automóveis no Brasil, em termos de prêmios de seguros. A empresa oferece seguros saúde, dental, auto, riscos elementares, pessoas, previdência privada, gestão de ativos e serviços de capitalização para mais de sete milhões de clientes. A Sul América tem uma rede de distribuição de 30,000 corretores independentes e parceiras com mais de 20 instituições financeiras de varejo com 16,000 pontos de venda. Listada na Bolsa de Valores de São Paulo BM&FBovespa, a Sul América SA registrou BRL 13.5bn (USD 5.02bn) em prêmios ganhos e um lucro líquido de 548.7mn (USD 204.2mn) em 2014. Os seus ativos totalizaram BRL 21.6bn (USD 8.04bn) em 31 de dezembro de 2014. A Healthways, Inc, fundada em 1981 e sediada em Cool Springs, Tennessee, EUA, é a maior fornecedora mundial independente de soluções de melhoria de bem-estar. The company's services allow customers of a Brazilian airline to accumulate points from a variety of customer loyalty programs in a single account and exchange them for prizes from a number of companies. Multiplus' network currently comprises more than 400 partners and has approximately 13 million participants that can accrue Multiplus points directly and indirectly in over 13,000 retail establishments. ORIGINAL: Canadian fertilizer manufacturer Potash Corp announced an agreement to purchase a 9.5% stake in Brazilian peer Fertilizantes Heringer SA from the latter's controlling shareholders Dalton Carlos Heringer, Dalton Dias Heringer and Juliana Heringer Rezende for USD 55.7mn. Subject of the transaction are 5,116,441 common shares and the deal is subject to regulatory approvals. Following the transaction, Heringer's capital structure will be as follows: Potash Corp with 10%, Carlos Heringer with 7.33%, Juliana Heringer with 7.27% and Dias Heringer with 46.39%. PotashCorp said the purchase is an important step in enhancing its global growth strategy and that it provides flexibility for its expanding New Brunswick operations. Fertilizantes Heringer SA, founded in 1968, ranks among the three largest fertilizer manufacturers in Brazil, with production capacity of six million metric tonnes per year. The company operates 21 mixing plants and business units, located in ten Brazilian states, and employs around 3,600 people. Fertilizantes Heringer SA is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange, and posted BRL 5.95bn (USD 2.51bn) in revenues and a net profit of BRL 7.96mn (USD 3.36mn) in 2014. Potash Corp, founded in 1989 and located in Saskatoon, Canada, is the world's largest fertilizer company by capacity, producing the three primary crop nutrients: potash, phosphate and nitrogen. The company is responsible for nearly one-fifth of global capacity through its Canadian operations. Potash Corp has operations and business interests in seven countries and over 5,000 employees. The company is listed on the Toronto (TSX) and New York (NYSE) Stock Exchanges, and had a market capitalisation of USD 29.9bn on 3 March 2015. ____________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 6 de Julho de 2015, o CADE aprovou a transacção. SoWiTec, established in 1993 and located in Sonnenbühl, Germany, focuses developing, financing, building and operating renewable energy projects across Latin America, Germany, Russia, Kazakhstan and Saudi Arabia. The investment round was led by Brazilian Angel Investor Joao Kepler with participation from Brazilian Angel Investors Marco Poli, Alcides Troller, Luis Rodeguero, Fernando Montovani, Jose Guiotti and Claudia Trotta. traktoPRO was founded in 2013 by 14-year freelancer Paulo Tenorio and mobile developer Jorge Henrique and is located in both Silicon Valley, California and Belo Horizonte, Brazil. traktoPRO is a startup that focuses on budgets and proposals to help the user to price the work, giving the freedom of choice, but calculating the margins of professional value for each hypothesis for the service being budgeted. traktoPRO is available on Google Play and Apple Store. The tool can also be used via web. The founding entrepreneurs have complementary specialties: Paulo Tenorio is a graphic designer with a long history in the market as a freelancer in Brazil and the United States, and extensive experience in sales and pricing: Jorge Henrique is a developer of mobile applications and is responsible for coordinating the traktoPRO project. __________________________________________________________________________ A traktoPRO, startup brasileira com operações nos EUA, disse que angariou um financiamento de capital por uma quantia não revelada. A ronda de investimento foi liderada pelo 'Angel Investor' brasileiro João Kepler com a co-participação dos 'Angel Investors' brasileiros Marco Poli, Alcides Troller, Luis Rodeguero, Fernando Montovani, José Guiotti e Claudia Trotta. A traktoPRO foi fundada em 2013 por Paulo Tenorio, freelancer com 14 anos de experiência, e pelo desenvolvedor móvel Jorge Henrique e está localizada conjuntamente em Silicon Valley, Califórnia, e Belo Horizonte, Brasil. A traktoPRO é uma startup que incide sobre os orçamentos e propostas para ajudar o usuário com o preço do trabalho, dando a liberdade de escolha, mas o cálculo das margens de valor profissional para cada hipótese para o serviço que está sendo orçamentado. 104513 23/02/2015 巴拿马 Seguros Banistmo SA 收购 Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA 哥伦比亚 投资银行及其他金融投资活动 (523); Bancolombia SA 商业银行及其他信贷服务 (522); 保险活动 (5241) 96.4 (官方数据) 100 哥伦比亚 并购 　 　 否 战略收购 完成的 现金 　 　 　 Arias & Muñoz; Towers Watson 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 1.38 　 　 　 UPDATE: On 31 August 2015, Grupo Sura announced that the transaction was completed. The sum of the deal stood at USD 96.4mn, which is equal to 1.38 times the equity of Seguros Banistmo at the end of August 2015. ORIGINAL: Colombian investment holding group Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (Grupo Sura) announced that it has agreed to acquire Panamanian insurer Seguros Banistmo from Colombian financial group Bancolombia for an undisclosed amount. Grupo Sura president Gonzalo Perez said that the purchase is an important step for the group's growth and consolidation in the region. Seguros Banistmo provides general insurance services such as auto, property, fire and theft insurance. The company had a total of four branches at the end of 2013. Grupo Sura is a Colombian investment holding company with investments in leading companies across Latin and Central America. The investment portfolio is mainly focused on the financial, insurance and social security sector, as well as in the industrial sector such as cement, energy, mining, real estate and food, among others. As of 30 September 2014, Grupo Sura reported total assets of approximately COP 38.3tn (USD 19.2bn). For FY ended 31 December 2013, it generated net income of around CLP 782.6bn (USD 332mn). 2015.12.03 　 96.40 　 　 　 　 　 负值 　 　 来源 1 来源 2 　 　 H1 2015 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　
104466 23/02/2015 埃及 Egyptian Company for Mobile Services - MobiNil 少数股权购买 Orange SA 法国 移动电信服务（卫星除外） (5172); Orascom Telecom Media And Technology Holding SAE 投资银行及其他金融投资活动 (523); 企业管理服务 (551); 数据处理、主机管理及相关服务 (518); 固定电信服务 (5171); 移动电信服务（卫星除外） (5172) 238.57 (官方数据) 5 中东北非 并购 　 　 否 战略收购 已公布 现金 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 　 4.32 13.8 71.06 负值 负值 3.62 11.55 　 French telecom Orange announced that it has signed an agreement to acquire an addition 5% stake in Egyptian Company for Mobile Services (ECMS) - MobilNil from local peer Orascom Telecom Media and Technology (OTMT) for EUR 209.6mn (USD 238.6mn). The shares will be acquired at a price of EGP 280.7 apiece, a 73% premium to the company's closing stock price of EGP 162.7 on 22 February 2015. Following the transaction, Orange will hold around a 99% stake in ECMS. The transaction is expected to complete in Q1 2015. ECMS, which operates under the brand name MobilNil, was founded in 1998. The company has 4299 sites, 36 switches and 25 mobile BTSs. It has 33 million customers. ECMS posted revenues of EGP 10.6bn (EUR 1.16bn) and net loss of EGP 456.7mn (EUR 50mn) in 2013. Orange is one of the world's leading telecommunications operators. The company is present in 30 countries in Europe, Asia and Africa, with a customer base of over 240 million people as of 30 September 2014. Its shares are listed on the NYSE Euronext Paris and on the New York Stock Exchange. It employs 159,000 people, and generated revenues of EUR 39.4bn and net income of EUR 925mn in 2014. OTMT is an investment holding company. The company's business activities are divided into three segments: GSM activities include mobile telecommunications operations; Media and Technology consists of OTVentures/Intouch Communications Service and the OTVentures Internet portals and other ventures; and the Cable businesses focuses on the management of cable networks. OTMT operates in Egypt, North Korea, Pakistan, Lebanon and other North African and Middle-Eastern countries. OTMT is listed on the Egyptian Stock Exchange.
